The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	 Pallekele: The West Indies cricket selectors on Monday named all-rounder Darren Sammy as captain for next months ODI series and a T20 international in Sri Lanka, according to a West Indies Cricket Board press release.    
	The squad: Darren Sammy (capt), Adrian Barath, Carlton Baugh, Sulieman Benn, Darren Bravo, Dwayne Bravo, Shivnarine Chanderpaul, Kirk Edwards, Chris Gayle, Nikita Miller, Kieron Pollard, Ravi Rampaul, Kemar Roach, Andre Russell, Devon Smith.         
	 New Delhi: They are the pillars of the Indian Test team but Rahul Dravid and VVS Laxman may have to lower their base prices in order to keep the franchises interested for the upcoming fourth edition of IPL.     
	Sources in the franchises said they would only be intersted in buying the two star batsmen if the duo lower their base price from Rs 92 lakh ($200,000) to the lower bracket of Rs 46 lakh ($ 100,000).        
	 Calcutta: International cricket will show its support for people living with HIV and Aids this week with leading players wearing red ribbons on their playing shirts in international matches to help celebrate World Aids Day as part of the Think Wise partnership.    
	Players and match officials will wear red ribbons in the ODIs to be played on Wednesday between Bangladesh-Zimbabwe, India-New Zealand, and Sri Lanka-West Indies, as well as on the opening day of the second Ashes Test on Friday.        
	 New Delhi: Following Indian middle distance runners stupendous show in Asian Games, theAFI will push for renewal of coach Nikolai Snesarevs contract till the London Olympics.        
	 New Delhi: The Indian sportspersons, who won gold in the Asian Games in Guangzhou, are likely to meet Prime Minister Manmohan Singh on December 4, officials said on Monday.        
	 New Delhi: All set to bid adieu to India after a bitter-sweet stint, chief hockey coach Jose Brasa, on Monday, said he deserved better from the system and refuted captain Rajpal Singhs allegations that he had been humiliating him.      
	New Delhi: The Indian football team will play against Qatar and Syria on December 19 and 26, respectively, in what will be their last two international friendlies in the lead up to the Asian Cup in January 2011.
    
	Maria makes it   
	New Delhi: Maria Rebello on Monday became the second Indian women referee to make it to AFC Elite Panel after her name was approved by the continental body.  
	Colaco honour   
	New Delhi: Former AIFF general secretary Alberto Colaco has been chosen for the Gold Star for AFC Distinguished Service Award 2011.                                                                                                                                                   
